  "dcterms:abstract": "The formation of toxic Amyloid β-peptide (Aβ) oligomers is one of the earliest events in the molecular pathology of Alzheimer’s Disease (AD). These oligomers lead to a variety of downstream effects, including impaired neuronal signaling, neuroinflammation, tau phosphorylation, and neurodegeneration. Here we show that a designed α-sheet peptide neutralizes the toxic effect of Aβ oligomers and serves as a capture agent in our soluble oligomer binding assay (SOBA).",
